Anna Okon A company in the logistics value chain of the industry, BMTC Logistics Limited, has said it developed total integrated solutions to uplift freight forwarding business in Nigeria. The Chief Executive Officer of BMTC, Audullahi Mosadoluwa, said this while explaining the comeback of the company and operations. He said BMTC had new ideas and capacity to move the business of freight forwarding in the country forward in the interest of the general public. He said, “We develop totally integrated solutions that foster communication between suppliers, manufacturers, distributors, and users by optimising the use of browser-based tools, cross-functional technologies, and e-business tools. “As one of the leading ocean freight forwarders, we offer efficient sea freight solutions customised to customers’ needs. “From full container loads  to less than container loads, on all major global routes, with guaranteed transit times, just as a major global air freight forwarding company, we take our delivery responsibility seriously. “While our primary responsibility lies in planning and monitoring every project, our logistics experts are geared towards  observing  and finding  different areas that will give you more expeditious results  -be it while meeting with project managers and suppliers to reviewing  material and equipment needed for transport.” Mosadoluwa said BMTC Logistics Limited had a presence in the United Kingdom and would be fully in China, India and Turkey before  May ending Copyright PUNCH.
